<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id522b1854-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6" identifier="/us/usc/t28/s99"><num value="99">§ 99.</num><heading> Maine</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Maine constitutes one judicial district.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I56" class="indent4 firstIndent-2">Court shall be held at Bangor and Portland.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id522b1855-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6">(<ref href="/us/act/1948-06-25/ch646">June 25, 1948, ch. 646</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/62/881">62 Stat. 881</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/95/573/s2">Pub. L. 95–573, § 2</ref>, <date date="1978-11-02">Nov. 2, 1978</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/92/2458">92 Stat. 2458</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id522b1856-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="historicalAndRevision" id="id522b1857-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Historical and Revision Notes</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Based on title 28, U.S.C., 1940 ed., § 160 (<ref href="/us/act/1911-03-03/ch231/s85">Mar. 3, 1911, ch. 231, § 85</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/36/1114">36 Stat. 1114</ref>; <ref href="/us/act/1911-12-22/ch7">Dec. 22, 1911, ch. 7</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/37/51">37 Stat. 51</ref>; <ref href="/us/act/1916-09-08/ch475">Sept. 8, 1916, ch. 475</ref>, §§ 1, 3, <ref href="/us/stat/39/850">39 Stat. 850</ref>; <ref href="/us/act/1923-03-04/ch279">Mar. 4, 1923, ch. 279</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/42/1506">42 Stat. 1506</ref>).</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Changes in arrangement and phraseology were made.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id522b1858-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="id522b1859-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1978—<ref href="/us/pl/95/573">Pub. L. 95–573</ref> struck out provision for two separate divisions, (1) the Northern Division comprising the counties of Aroostook, Hancock, Penobscot, Piscataquis, Somerset, Waldo, and Washington and (2) the Southern Division comprising the counties of Androscoggin, Cumberland, Franklin, Kennebec, Knox, Lincoln, Oxford, Sagadahoc, and York.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="id522b185a-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDateOfAmendment" id="id522b185b-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date of 1978 Amendment</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Amendment by <ref href="/us/pl/95/573">Pub. L. 95–573</ref> effective 180 days after <date date="1978-11-02">Nov. 2, 1978</date>, see <ref href="/us/pl/95/573/s6">section 6 of Pub. L. 95–573</ref>, set out as a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t28/s93">section 93 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
